---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Worship — Praying Inside the Story"
  description="A six-step Ignatian Contemplation framework for entering a Gospel scene with your imagination — stepping into Scripture as a participant, not just a reader."
>
  <a class="overlay-back" href="/worship/takeaways/">&#8592; Back to Takeaways</a>
  <a class="overlay-close" href="/" aria-label="Close">&times;</a>

  <div class="takeaways-content pp-page">
    <span class="takeaways-tag">Worship</span>
    <h1 class="takeaways-title">Praying Inside the Story</h1>
    <p class="pp-subtitle">Six steps for entering a Gospel scene — and letting it speak to you.</p>

    <!-- Quick-jump nav -->
    <div class="pp-nav">
      <a class="pp-nav-link" href="#step-settle">1. Settle</a>
      <a class="pp-nav-link" href="#step-choose">2. Choose a Scene</a>
      <a class="pp-nav-link" href="#step-enter">3. Enter the Story</a>
      <a class="pp-nav-link" href="#step-stay">4. Stay &amp; Notice</a>
      <a class="pp-nav-link" href="#step-speak">5. Speak with Jesus</a>
      <a class="pp-nav-link" href="#step-receive">6. Receive &amp; Record</a>
    </div>

    <div class="pp-grid">

      <!-- STEP 1: SETTLE -->
      <article class="pp-card" id="step-settle">
        <div class="pp-card-top">
          <h2 class="pp-day">Step 1</h2>
          <div class="pp-mode-badge">Settle</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-card-body">
          <p class="pp-guide">Before you open Scripture, open yourself. Find a quiet place and sit comfortably. Take three slow, deliberate breaths. Let the noise of your day — the to-do list, the phone, the unfinished conversations — fall away. Silently invite the Holy Spirit to lead your imagination. This is not a mental exercise; it is a prayer. You are not trying to conjure a feeling — you are asking God to use your mind as a means of meeting with Him. Stay here for two or three minutes before moving on.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- STEP 2: CHOOSE A SCENE -->
      <article class="pp-card" id="step-choose">
        <div class="pp-card-top">
          <h2 class="pp-day">Step 2</h2>
          <div class="pp-mode-badge">Choose a Scene</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-card-body">
          <p class="pp-guide">Select one Gospel passage — ideally a scene with movement, tension, or a direct encounter with Jesus. Read it through slowly, twice. Don't analyze it yet. Just let the story settle in your mind. If nothing comes to you, start with one of these: the calming of the storm (Mark 4:35–41), the woman caught in adultery (John 8:1–11), the blind man calling out on the road (Mark 10:46–52), or Jesus with Mary and Martha (Luke 10:38–42). Shorter, more vivid scenes work better than long discourses. You want action, people, and place.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- STEP 3: ENTER THE STORY -->
      <article class="pp-card" id="step-enter">
        <div class="pp-card-top">
          <h2 class="pp-day">Step 3</h2>
          <div class="pp-mode-badge">Enter the Story</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-card-body">
          <p class="pp-guide">Close your eyes and step inside the scene. This is what Ignatius called the "composition of place" — building the setting in your mind with as much sensory detail as possible. What does the ground feel like underfoot? What do you smell — salt water, dust, bread, sweat? What sounds are in the background? What time of day is it? Where is the light coming from? Decide your role: Are you a bystander watching from the edge of the crowd? A disciple at Jesus' side? The person being healed or confronted? There is no wrong answer — choose where you feel drawn. Then let the scene begin to move.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- STEP 4: STAY & NOTICE -->
      <article class="pp-card" id="step-stay">
        <div class="pp-card-top">
          <h2 class="pp-day">Step 4</h2>
          <div class="pp-mode-badge">Stay &amp; Notice</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-card-body">
          <p class="pp-guide">Let the scene unfold without forcing it. Watch what happens. Watch what you feel. Don't rush to the "spiritual lesson" — stay in the experience. Pay close attention to moments of consolation (warmth, peace, longing, tears, joy) and moments of desolation (resistance, fear, numbness, the urge to stop). Both are data. Notice what surprises you — a detail in the scene you didn't expect, a reaction you didn't anticipate in yourself, a moment where Jesus looks at you or speaks directly to you. These are often the most important moments of the whole prayer. Sit here for at least five minutes. Longer is better.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- STEP 5: SPEAK WITH JESUS -->
      <article class="pp-card" id="step-speak">
        <div class="pp-card-top">
          <h2 class="pp-day">Step 5</h2>
          <div class="pp-mode-badge">Speak with Jesus</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-card-body">
          <p class="pp-guide">Ignatius called this the "colloquy" — a heart-to-heart conversation. Still inside the scene, turn toward Jesus and speak honestly. Not formally. Not piously. The way you'd talk to someone who already knows everything about you and loves you anyway. Tell Him what you felt during the scene. Tell Him what confused you, what frightened you, what moved you. Ask Him what He wants you to understand. Then be quiet and listen. You may sense a response — a word, an image, a feeling of peace or conviction. Receive whatever comes without forcing it. The goal isn't to hear an audible voice; it's to be genuinely present with the One you're talking to.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- STEP 6: RECEIVE & RECORD -->
      <article class="pp-card" id="step-receive">
        <div class="pp-card-top">
          <h2 class="pp-day">Step 6</h2>
          <div class="pp-mode-badge">Receive &amp; Record</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-card-body">
          <p class="pp-guide">Slowly come back out of the scene. Open your eyes. Before anything else, pick up a pen and write down one word, one image, or one sentence that captures what lingered. Not a summary — just what stayed. This small act of writing is how you bring the encounter back into your daily life, and how you start to notice patterns across multiple sessions. Over time, your journal becomes a record of what God is saying to you through Scripture — not what the commentaries say, but what He said to you specifically, in those scenes, on those days. Carry the image or word into your day. Return to it before you sleep.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

    </div><!-- /.pp-grid -->

    <!-- Suggested Scenes -->
    <div class="pp-scenes-section">
      <span class="pp-scenes-label">Suggested Scenes to Try</span>
      <div class="pp-scenes-grid">
        <div class="pp-scene-item">
          <span class="pp-scene-ref">Mark 4:35–41</span>
          <span class="pp-scene-title">The Storm on the Sea</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-scene-item">
          <span class="pp-scene-ref">John 8:1–11</span>
          <span class="pp-scene-title">The Woman Caught in Adultery</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-scene-item">
          <span class="pp-scene-ref">Mark 10:46–52</span>
          <span class="pp-scene-title">Blind Bartimaeus</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-scene-item">
          <span class="pp-scene-ref">Luke 10:38–42</span>
          <span class="pp-scene-title">Mary &amp; Martha</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-scene-item">
          <span class="pp-scene-ref">Matthew 14:22–33</span>
          <span class="pp-scene-title">Walking on Water</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-scene-item">
          <span class="pp-scene-ref">John 20:11–18</span>
          <span class="pp-scene-title">Mary at the Tomb</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-scene-item">
          <span class="pp-scene-ref">Luke 15:11–32</span>
          <span class="pp-scene-title">The Prodigal Son</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-scene-item">
          <span class="pp-scene-ref">John 21:1–19</span>
          <span class="pp-scene-title">Breakfast on the Shore</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- AI Prompt -->
    <div class="pp-ai-prompt">
      <span class="pp-ai-label">AI Prompt</span>
      <p>I want to practice Ignatian Contemplation. Walk me through each of the six steps one at a time, pausing after each to ask me the reflection questions. Don't move on until I've answered honestly — push back gently if my responses feel surface-level. Help me stay inside the scene rather than jumping to analysis. At the end, help me write a short journal entry capturing what I noticed and what I want to carry into my week.</p>
    </div>

  </div><!-- /.takeaways-content -->
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

  /* ─── Page header ───────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .pp-subtitle {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: #7a7368;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ─── Quick-jump nav ────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .pp-nav {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 1.75rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(183, 156, 92, 0.2);
  }

  .pp-nav-link {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #7a7368;
    background: rgba(70, 61, 52, 0.04);
    border: 1px solid rgba(199, 187, 170, 0.5);
    padding: 0.3rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 2px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .pp-nav-link:hover {
    background: #6a6156;
    color: #f3efe9;
    border-color: #6a6156;
  }

  /* ─── Card grid ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .pp-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  /* ─── Individual card ───────────────────────────────────────── */
  .pp-card {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
    border: 1px solid rgba(199, 187, 170, 0.45);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    transition: box-shadow 0.25s;
  }

  .pp-card:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(70, 61, 52, 0.09);
  }

  /* ─── Card header ───────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .pp-card-top {
    background: rgba(70, 61, 52, 0.04);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(199, 187, 170, 0.4);
    padding: 1.1rem 1.2rem 1rem;
  }

  .pp-day {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #3d3830;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .pp-descriptors {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    color: #9e8c78;
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }

  .pp-mode-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #f3efe9;
    background: #8a7e6e;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.65rem;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  /* ─── Card body ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .pp-card-body {
    padding: 1.1rem 1.2rem 1rem;
    flex: 1;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .pp-guide {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #5e554b;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
    padding-bottom: 0.9rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(199, 187, 170, 0.3);
  }

  /* ─── Reflect section ───────────────────────────────────────── */
  .pp-reflect-section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-top: auto;
  }

  .pp-reflect-label {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.58rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #b79c5c;
  }

  .pp-reflect-list {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .pp-reflect-list li {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: #5e554b;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ─── Suggested Scenes ──────────────────────────────────────── */
  .pp-scenes-section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
    border: 1px solid rgba(199, 187, 170, 0.45);
    border-radius: 6px;
  }

  .pp-scenes-label {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.58rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #b79c5c;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .pp-scenes-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .pp-scene-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.2rem;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    background: rgba(70, 61, 52, 0.03);
    border: 1px solid rgba(199, 187, 170, 0.35);
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .pp-scene-ref {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: #8a7e6e;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .pp-scene-title {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #3d3830;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  /* ─── AI Prompt ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .pp-ai-prompt {
    background: rgba(70, 61, 52, 0.04);
    border: 1px solid rgba(199, 187, 170, 0.45);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .pp-ai-label {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.58rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #f3efe9;
    background: #6a6156;
    padding: 0.3rem 0.65rem;
    border-radius: 2px;
    margin-top: 0.1rem;
  }

  .pp-ai-prompt p {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 0.93rem;
    color: #5e554b;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ─── Responsive ────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  @media (max-width: 1100px) {
    .pp-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
    .pp-scenes-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .pp-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .pp-scenes-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }

    .pp-ai-prompt {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }

    .pp-day {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>
